Do you want Hotjar to not collect your data?

   At Hotjar we take your privacy very seriously. Access to your data is
   limited to the website owner and is processed and stored in a way to
   protect you and your information.

   That said, we don’t want anyone feeling unsure of how their data is
   being handled and you can choose to opt-out of Hotjar by following the
   instructions below.
   Your browser ( ) currently supports one-click opt-out. Simply click the
   button below to opt-out from Hotjar processing your data.
   Your browser does not currently support one-click opt-out. To opt-out
   from Hotjar processing your data, please follow the instructions below
   to enable “Do Not Track” in your browser. Note that this will also opt
   you out of similar services which use the “Do Not Track” setting to
   disable tracking.

You've Opted-Out of Hotjar on this Browser

   To change this, click the button below.
   (BUTTON) Enable Hotjar

You've Opted-Out of Hotjar on this Browser by enabling Do Not Track mode

   If you wish to opt-in, please disable Do Not Track mode in your
   browser.

You've not Opted-Out of Hotjar on this Browser

   To change this, click the button below.
   (BUTTON) Disable Hotjar

   Note: Clearing your cookies, running in incognito/private mode, or
   using a different browser will enable tracking again.
   As your browser is updated to newer versions, the one-click opt-out
   above may stop working. As an alternative, we recommend activating the
   “Do Not Track” setting in your browser by following the below
   instructions. This will also opt you out of similar services which use
   the “Do Not Track” setting to disable tracking.

One-click opt-out is currently supported by the following browsers:

How to install the Do Not Track header

    1. To opt-out, please go to Safari preferences (cmd + , or click
       "Safari" > "Preferences..." in the menu bar).
    2. Click on "Privacy".
    3. Tick the "Ask websites not to track me" checkbox.

   safari-11-do-not-track

   For more information, please visit the documentation.
    1. To opt-out, please go to Safari settings on your iOS device.
    2. Enable the "Ask Websites Not To Track Me" toggle.

   safari-ios11-do-not-track.jpg

   For more information, please visit the documentation.
    1. To opt-out, please go to Firefox preferences (cmd + , or click
       "Firefox" > "Preferences..." in the menu bar).
    2. Click on "Privacy & Security".
    3. In the "Content Blocking" section under Send websites a "Do Not
       Track" signal that you don't want to be tracked, choose "Always".

   firefox-mac-do-not-track

   For more information, please visit the documentation.
    1. To opt-out, please go to Firefox "Options" from the menu button.
    2. Click on "Privacy & Security".
    3. In the "Content Blocking" section under Send websites a "Do Not
       Track" signal that you don't want to be tracked, choose "Always".

   firefox-win-do-not-track

   For more information, please visit the documentation.

   This feature requires iOS version 11.
    1. To opt-out, please tap the menu button at the bottom of the screen.
    2. Turn on the switch next to "Tracking Protection".

   firefox-ios-do-not-track

   For more information, please visit the documentation.
    1. To opt-out, please go to Firefox "Settings" from the menu button.
    2. Click on "Privacy".
    3. Turn on the "Do not track" switch.

   firefox-mobile-do-not-track

   For more information, please visit the documentation.
    1. To opt-out, please go to Chrome settings (cmd + , or click "Chrome"
       > "Preferences..." in the menu bar).
    2. At the bottom click "Advanced".
    3. Under "Privacy and security" turn Send a "Do Not Track" request
       with your browsing traffic on.

   chrome-mac-do-not-track

   For more information, please visit the documentation.
    1. To opt-out, please go to Chrome "Settings" from the menu button.
    2. At the bottom click "Advanced".
    3. Under "Privacy and security" turn Send a "Do Not Track" request
       with your browsing traffic on.

   chrome-win-do-not-track

   For more information, please visit the documentation.
    1. To opt-out, please go to Chrome "Settings" from the menu button.
    2. Click on "Privacy".
    3. Click on "Do Not Track".
    4. Turn on the switch.

   chrome-mobile-do-not-track

   For more information, please visit the documentation.

   This feature is not available on iOS at the moment.
   For more information, please visit the documentation.
    1. To opt-out, please go to Opera preferences (cmd + , or click
       "Opera" > "Preferences..." in the menu bar).
    2. Click on "Advanced".
    3. Click on "Privacy & Security".
    4. Under "Privacy and security" turn the Send a "Do Not Track" request
       with your browsing traffic switch on.

   opera-mac-do-not-track

   For more information, please visit the documentation.
    1. To opt-out, please go to Opera settings (alt + P or click "Menu" >
       "Settings").
    2. Click on "Advanced".
    3. Click on "Privacy & Security".
    4. Under "Privacy and security" turn the Send a "Do Not Track" request
       with your browsing traffic switch on.

   opera-win-do-not-track

   For more information, please visit the documentation.
    1. To opt-out, please go to IE tools (cog wheel icon).
    2. Click on "Safety".
    3. Click on "Turn on Do Not Track requests".
    4. In the confirmation dialog click "Turn on".

   ie-do-not-track

   ie-do-not-track-2

   For more information, please visit the documentation.
    1. To opt-out, please go to IE "Settings" from the menu button.
    2. Click on "advanced settings".
    3. Check the Send a Do Not Track request to websites you visit box.

   ie-mobile-do-not-track

   For more information, please visit the documentation.
    1. To opt-out, please go to Edge "Settings" from the menu button.
    2. Click on "Privacy & Security".
    3. Turn the Send Do Not Track requests switch on.

   edge-do-not-track

   For more information, please visit the documentation.
